<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="467" pageId="8" pageNumber="466" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1703,2016]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1435,151,213]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="467" pageId="8" pageNumber="466">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1919,1944]" pageId="8" pageNumber="466">Remarks.</emphasis>
The description of this species was based on the presence of two sharp keels along the whole shell instead of only one and two in the last whorl from congeneric and sympatric 
<taxonomicName box="[1068,1215,1955,1979]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cochlespiridae" genus="Aforia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="466" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="magnifica">
<emphasis box="[1068,1215,1955,1979]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="466">A. magnifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The shell of both 
<collectingCountry box="[151,255,1991,2016]" name="Antarctica" pageId="8" pageNumber="466">Antarctic</collectingCountry>
species is truly variable. The radula presented no perceptible differences between forms. The real status of 
<taxonomicName box="[182,355,151,176]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cochlespiridae" genus="Aforia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="multispiralis">
<emphasis box="[182,199,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[214,355,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">multispiralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains somewhat dubious. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wiese" box="[684,836,151,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" refString="Wiese, V. (2001) Comments on a &quot; new &quot; Turrid species from Kerguelen. Schrifte zur Malakozoologie aus dem Haus der Natur - Cismar, 18, 33 - 34." type="journal article" year="2001">
Wiese (
<number box="[769,827,152,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
illustrated the 
<typeStatus box="[1005,1103,151,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bozzetti, 1997" authorityName="Bozzetti" authorityYear="1997" box="[1142,1373,151,176]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cochlespiridae" genus="Danilacarina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="elenae">
<emphasis box="[1142,1373,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">Danilacarina elenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Kerguelen Is. and corroborated the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName box="[701,873,188,213]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cochlespiridae" genus="Aforia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="multispiralis">
<emphasis box="[701,873,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">A. multispiralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
